Opens up the center, especially trying to take advantage with the e5 pawn push due to the weakness of the bishop on d6.

e5 here helps Black by developing his bishop to the more active c5 square though. 
More importantly Black cannot play Nf6 because of e5 Qe7 Qe2 losing a piece. Also Black cannot play Ne7 because Ng5 0-0 Qh5 loses material.
